circumstances.circumstances:
Andreas suffers from Schizophrenia and was recently released from the hospital. He was very agitated at the time of his disappearance and was delusional. He had begun speaking to family members and friends about cleansing himself in the River for God.

His car, shoes, and wallet were found near the Riverfront Park Boat Ramp in Leavenworth, KS.

At the time of Andreas' disappearance the Missouri River was at its highest in decades and had washed away several encampments and killed dozens.

Andreas had multiple reconstructive surgeries on his face and mouth due to a rare disorder called Parry Romberg. Due to the surgeries there may be extensive or abnormal hardware or wiring on the lower and possibly upper jaw. Dental anomalies may be present as well.

circumstances.circumstances:
Paula Godfrey disappeared on September 1st 1984, her disappearance has been linked to suspected serial killer John Edward Robinson Sr. Robinson picked Godfrey up at her parents home and said he would drive her to the airport, she has never been seen again. Robinson had allegedly hired Godfey to be a sales representative for his management consulting company Equi-11. Godfey is one of three women whose disappearances in the 1980s authorities have linked to Robinson, the other women are Lisa Stasi and Catherine Clampitt. Robinson was convicted of the murder of Lisa Stasi in October 2002. Robinson is charged with killing five women.
Godfrey was an accomplished amateur figure skater before her 1984 disappearance.

circumstances.circumstances: Catherine Clampitt moved to Overland Park Kansas in 1987, she was born in Korea, but grew up in Texas after being adopted. She was employed by John Edward Robinson Sr. to work at his management consulting firm Equi-11. After not hearing from her since June 15th 1987, she was reported missing. Clampitt's case is connected to the disappearance of Lisa Stasi and Paula Godfrey. Robinson was convicted of the murder of Lisa Stasi in October 2002. Robinson is charged with killing five women.

circumstances.circumstances:
Tony was last seen by his wife at Jerry Ivey Park in south Salina, KS on 08/17/1987.

His wife saw him driving east on his way home from work at Beech Aircraft Corp in Wichita. She followed him to the park where he parked near the restrooms. Tony was surprised to see her and told her he was not feeling well. He would not let her drive him home, so she left him to get her brother's help. When she returned to the park, the car was still parked by the restrooms. The vehicle was locked and Tony's possessions were still inside.

Tony didn't show up for work the next day. His wife reported him missing on 05/19/1987. He has not contacted anyone in his family to let them know he is alive.

Tony was devoted to both his children and the disappearance was uncharacteristic. He had been living in Salina for about nine years. Tony is originally from New York. His parents emigrated from Italy and settled on Thompson Street in Greenwich Village before moving to Astoria.
